Build - 20020109 
If eclipse is started with open editors for .java files that have been removed 
from the project outside of eclipse, you receive an error dialog containing "An 
error has occured while restoring the workbench: See error log for more 
details."  This is followed (and initially hidden) by multiple Internal error 
dialogs containing "An internal error has occured. Failed to execute runnable 
(java.lang.NullPointerException) See error log for more details."  Clicking OK 
for each of the error dialogs allows eclipse to continue coming up.

The below scenario seems to always generate 1 error dialog and 2 internal error 
dialogs.  However, I have seen more than 15 internal error dialogs generated 
under similar situations, possibly missing .classpath file for project.


Steps to recreate:
1. Create a dummy Java project and add a dummy class
2. Open the class in the editor in a Java perspective
3. Shutdown Eclipse
4. Delete the dummy class from the file system outside of eclipse
5. Startup Eclipse, receive error messages
